"title": "5931: resistance",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5931",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Opposition to the demands of the state or other legitimate authorities. Individuals must not resist such demands unless they are contrary to God's requirements. God will himself judge unjust rulers. Christians should not resist the evil person but, following Jesus Christ's teaching and example, entrust themselves to God.</p>\n<h2>God should not be resisted</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:21\">2CH 35:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:51\">ACT 7:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:17\">ACT 11:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:19\">ROM 9:19</a></p>\n<h2>Individuals should not resist legitimate authorities</h2>\n<h3>Civil authorities</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1-Rom13:2\">ROM 13:1–13:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:12-Deut17:13\">DEU 17:12–17:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:6\">1SA 24:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:1-Titus3:2\">TIT 3:1–3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:13-1Pet2:14\">1PE 2:13–2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:17\">1PE 2:17</a></p>\n<h3>Religious authorities</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:17\">HEB 13:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:5\">ACT 23:5</a></p>\n<h3>Parental authority</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:1\">EPH 6:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:20\">COL 3:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:2\">2TI 3:2</a></p>\n<h2>Resistance of unjust authorities</h2>\n<h3>Resistance to human authorities is justified when they oppose God's requirements</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:15-Exod1:17\">EXO 1:15–1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:22-Exod2:3\">EXO 1:22–2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:13-Dan3:18\">DAN 3:13–3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:6-Dan6:10\">DAN 6:6–6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:18-Acts4:20\">ACT 4:18–4:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:27-Acts5:29\">ACT 5:27–5:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:23\">HEB 11:23</a></p>\n<h3>God will enable Christians, unjustly brought before human authorities, to defend themselves</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:11\">MRK 13:11</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:19-Matt10:20\">MAT 10:19–10:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:11-Luke12:12\">LUK 12:11–12:12</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:14-Luke21:15\">LUK 21:14–21:15</a></p>\n<h3>God will vindicate those of his people who cannot resist unjust authorities</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:28-Dan3:29\">DAN 3:28–3:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:20-Gen39:21\">GEN 39:20–39:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl8:12\">ECC 8:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:19-Dan6:28\">DAN 6:19–6:28</a></p>\n<h3>God will himself judge unjust rulers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:10\">HOS 5:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:15-1Kgs21:19\">1KI 21:15–21:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:23-Isa1:26\">ISA 1:23–1:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:11-Isa3:15\">ISA 3:11–3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:1-Isa10:3\">ISA 10:1–10:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:14-Isa59:20\">ISA 59:14–59:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:27-Ezek22:31\">EZK 22:27–22:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:2-Mic7:4\">MIC 7:2–7:4</a></p>\n<h2>Resisting evil</h2>\n<h3>Christians should not resist the evil person</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:38-Matt5:41\">MAT 5:38–5:41</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:43-Matt5:48\">MAT 5:43–5:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:52\">MAT 26:52</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:27-Luke6:30\">LUK 6:27–6:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:19-Rom12:21\">ROM 12:19–12:21</a></p>\n<h3>Christians should follow the teaching and example of Jesus Christ and entrust themselves to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:20-1Pet2:23\">1PE 2:20–2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:7-Isa53:9\">ISA 53:7–53:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:14\">2TI 4:14</a></p>",
